Sentencas: The expedition of cathode materials with high stability, superior catalytic activity and better electrochemical performance is critical for realizing the commercial application of solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A highly stable cobalt-free LaBa0.5Sr0.5Fe2O6-δ oxide as a high performance cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, we report a cobalt-free LaBa0.5Sr0.5Fe2O6-delta oxide as the cathode material and systematically evaluate its physical and electrochemical properties.
Titulo: A highly stable cobalt-free LaBa0.5Sr0.5Fe2O6-δ oxide as a high performance cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The research results indicate that this material exhibits the perovskite-typed structure and possesses a good high-temperature chemical compatibility and interface stability with the Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 electrolyte.
Titulo: A highly stable cobalt-free LaBa0.5Sr0.5Fe2O6-δ oxide as a high performance cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C, theLaBa(0.5)Sr(0.5)Fe(2)O(6-delta) cathode shows the lowest polarization resistance and the maximum power density with the values of 0.152 Omega cm(2) and 370 mWcm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: A highly stable cobalt-free LaBa0.5Sr0.5Fe2O6-δ oxide as a high performance cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, there is almost no significant change in the polarization resistance and output power density during the 100 h stability test.
Titulo: A highly stable cobalt-free LaBa0.5Sr0.5Fe2O6-δ oxide as a high performance cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen partial pressure dependence studies indicate that the determining steps are the transfer process of oxygen ions from the cathode to the electrolyte, the charge-transfer process and the adsorption process of oxygen molecules on the electrode surface.
Titulo: A highly stable cobalt-free LaBa0.5Sr0.5Fe2O6-δ oxide as a high performance cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The preliminary results suggest that the LaBa0.5Sr0.5Fe2O6-delta oxide is expected to be a promising cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells.
